Privacy Policy for the getPopulationRadius Custom Action

Last updated: May 7, 2025

This Privacy Policy describes how the getPopulationRadius custom action (“Action”) used within ChatGPT (“Service”) collects, uses, retains, and shares personal information when you request a population estimate for a geographic radius.

1. Information We Collect
User-Provided Data:

Latitude and longitude coordinates.

Radius (in miles).

Year for which the population estimate is requested.

Technical Metadata:

IP address of the Service at the time of the API call (collected by RapidAPI).

Request timestamps and usage metrics (e.g., number of calls, response times).

2. How We Use Your Information
Primary Purpose:
We forward your inputs to the Population Inside Radius API solely to retrieve the population estimate for the specified location, radius, and year.

Service Improvement:
Aggregated, de-identified usage data may be analyzed to monitor and improve performance, reliability, and user experience.

3. Data Retention
User-Provided Inputs:
Not stored by the Action or by OpenAI—forwarded live to the API provider and then discarded.

Technical Metadata:
Retained by RapidAPI for up to 90 days for operational monitoring, analytics, and auditing, after which it is automatically purged.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
With Population Inside Radius API Provider:
Your inputs are transmitted to the population-inside-radius service (via RapidAPI). The provider processes the inputs solely to generate the population estimate and is bound by its own privacy policy.

No Other Third-Party Sharing:
We do not sell or share your inputs or results with any other third parties.

5. Security
All API requests are made over HTTPS (TLS 1.2+).

API keys are stored encrypted and never exposed in client-side code.

Access to logs and infrastructure is restricted to authorized personnel only.

6. Your Rights
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

Access or obtain a copy of the personal data we hold.

Rectify inaccurate or incomplete data.

Delete or request erasure of personal data.

Restrict or object to certain processing activities.

Withdraw Consent at any time by discontinuing use of the Action.

7. Compliance
GDPR: We comply with the EU General Data Protection Regulation for users in the European Economic Area.

CCPA: California residents have rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act.

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy to reflect changes in practices or legal requirements. We will notify you by updating the “Last updated” date above.

If you have any questions or concerns about this policy, please reach out to aloha@aloh.ai.
